    "prompt": "<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of two blocks, labeled X and Y, which are connected by a string that passes over a pulley. Block Y is larger than Block X and is suspended higher above a horizontal surface than Block X.\" height=\"241\" src=\"/images/09a0e7eb735b0435eaa719f403cbfff6.png\" width=\"185\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Blocks <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Y</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> are connected by a string that passes over a pulley, as shown in the figure. Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Y</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> has more mass than Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. The string and pulley have negligible mass, and the pulley rotates with negligible friction. After the blocks are released from rest, what happens to the mechanical energy <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub mechanical\"><math alttext=\"E sub mechanical\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mtext>mech</mtext></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of the system consisting of the two blocks and Earth?</p>\n",
